WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.478 --> 00:00:07.980
<i>Previously on</i>
Criminal Minds: Evolution...

2
00:00:08.114 --> 00:00:09.315
Sophisticated.

3
00:00:09.416 --> 00:00:11.418
You see that? Another Haeberlin.

4
00:00:11.484 --> 00:00:13.520
<i>We thought
these cases were connected.</i>

5
00:00:13.620 --> 00:00:15.655
<i>Now we have our smoking gun.</i>

6
00:00:15.755 --> 00:00:18.324
<i>The unsub gathered followers
that he's now activating.</i>

7
00:00:18.458 --> 00:00:22.294
This is a network. Whatever city
Sicarius finds himself.

8
00:00:22.361 --> 00:00:24.697
<i>Second Street is his
preferred hunting ground.</i>

9
00:00:24.797 --> 00:00:26.599
Did you come here to kill me?

10
00:00:26.666 --> 00:00:27.967
I already killed you
an hour ago.

11
00:00:28.067 --> 00:00:31.438
I just came here
to watch an old man die.

12
00:00:31.504 --> 00:00:32.705
I always knew it.

13
00:00:32.805 --> 00:00:35.141
Family's what gets you killed.

14
00:00:35.241 --> 00:00:37.710
Our vice is in our blood.

15
00:00:37.844 --> 00:00:39.979
- You are?
- You know who I am.

16
00:00:40.079 --> 00:00:41.414
You killed my sister.

17
00:00:41.514 --> 00:00:42.682
<i>Alison.</i>

18
00:00:42.782 --> 00:00:45.284
Your subconscious
is fighting urges to kill.

19
00:00:45.351 --> 00:00:47.854
which is why
I'm distracting you.

20
00:00:47.954 --> 00:00:50.256
You talking to me
is how you cope.

21
00:00:50.356 --> 00:00:54.126
You think. if I walk you
through everything.

22
00:00:54.193 --> 00:00:56.062
you'll be able
to stop someone else?

23
00:00:56.162 --> 00:00:58.197
You're a living resource. Elias.

24
00:00:58.297 --> 00:00:59.699
For the sake of others.

25
00:00:59.799 --> 00:01:02.101
I can't just let you sit in here
and not tell your story.

26
00:01:02.201 --> 00:01:04.303
The families of some of your
victims have reached out.

27
00:01:04.370 --> 00:01:06.405
and they want to meet you.

28
00:01:06.539 --> 00:01:08.040
It was part of your training.

29
00:01:08.140 --> 00:01:09.709
- What?
- Your training.

30
00:01:09.809 --> 00:01:13.079
- By this government agency.
- Where did you hear that?

31
00:01:13.212 --> 00:01:14.581
It's in the podcast.

32
00:01:14.681 --> 00:01:16.716
Welcome to <i>The Sicarius Files.</i>

33
00:01:16.816 --> 00:01:18.451
May I call you Elias?

34
00:01:19.586 --> 00:01:20.653
Oh.

35
00:01:21.554 --> 00:01:24.323
Look at me. Brian.
It's sad how pathetic I am.

36
00:01:24.423 --> 00:01:25.558
but you know
what's even more pathetic?

37
00:01:25.658 --> 00:01:27.326
Someone who makes
a show about it

38
00:01:27.426 --> 00:01:30.062
<i>and anyone who listens to it.</i>

39
00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:38.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

40
00:01:39.572 --> 00:01:42.374
<i>So true.</i>

41
00:01:44.777 --> 00:01:46.178
Mmm.

42
00:01:46.245 --> 00:01:48.247
- This carbonara is to die for.
- I know. right?

43
00:01:48.347 --> 00:01:50.016
Where's this place again?

44
00:01:50.116 --> 00:01:52.184
It just opened up
on Second Street.

45
00:01:52.251 --> 00:01:54.186
around the corner
from my office.

46
00:01:54.286 --> 00:01:55.321
Mama. look!

47
00:01:56.523 --> 00:01:57.924
It's for Auntie Ryleigh.

48
00:01:58.024 --> 00:02:00.793
Oh! Thank you. sweetie.

49
00:02:00.893 --> 00:02:02.194
It's almost time for bed now.

50
00:02:02.261 --> 00:02:03.596
Do you need help
brushing your teeth?

51
00:02:03.696 --> 00:02:06.265
- No.
- Okay.

52
00:02:11.103 --> 00:02:13.806
She gets it from her mama.

53
00:02:13.940 --> 00:02:15.942
I hate to break it to you.
big sis. but

54
00:02:16.042 --> 00:02:18.978
everybody thinks they got
good taste and a sense of humor.

55
00:02:19.111 --> 00:02:22.481
but they couldn't possibly
all have good taste.

56
00:02:22.615 --> 00:02:25.885
Very funny.
I know that movie. too.

57
00:02:25.985 --> 00:02:27.554
Is that why you haven't
uttered one word

58
00:02:27.620 --> 00:02:29.288
about what I've done
to the kitchen?

59
00:02:30.422 --> 00:02:31.457
The new backsplash?

60
00:02:31.558 --> 00:02:33.259
Kali.

61
00:02:33.325 --> 00:02:35.562
- What?
- Those colors.

62
00:02:35.662 --> 00:02:36.796
What were you thinking?

63
00:02:36.896 --> 00:02:38.731
Those colors
announce themselves.

64
00:02:38.798 --> 00:02:41.634
Yeah. they scream.
"I got bad taste."

65
00:02:41.734 --> 00:02:43.870
Oh.

66
00:02:43.970 --> 00:02:46.539
Is everything okay?

67
00:02:46.639 --> 00:02:48.140
It's just my mom. She fell.

68
00:02:48.274 --> 00:02:50.409
Again.

69
00:02:50.476 --> 00:02:52.078
Was your dad home?

70
00:02:52.178 --> 00:02:54.681
No. but the neighbor was able
to get her to the hospital.

71
00:02:54.814 --> 00:02:57.483
I know. You need to be there.

72
00:02:57.584 --> 00:02:58.985
I'm sorry. babe.

73
00:02:59.085 --> 00:03:00.987
No. I'm sorry. It's getting
out of hand. I don't...

74
00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:02.822
There's nothing
to be sorry about.

75
00:03:02.922 --> 00:03:04.090
I'll call you as soon
as I can. okay?

76
00:03:04.190 --> 00:03:05.858
- Mm.
- Okay.

77
00:03:09.696 --> 00:03:12.699
- I love you.
- I love you more.

78
00:03:19.105 --> 00:03:20.339
Look.

79
00:03:20.439 --> 00:03:21.974
If there's anything
you or Avery need

80
00:03:22.074 --> 00:03:23.375
while he's gone.

81
00:03:23.475 --> 00:03:25.778
do not hesitate to reach out
to me or Jesse.

82
00:03:25.845 --> 00:03:27.847
I appreciate that.

83
00:03:27.980 --> 00:03:29.782
Especially...

84
00:03:29.849 --> 00:03:32.451
if you want Jesse
to replace that backsplash.

85
00:03:32.518 --> 00:03:35.387
Girl.

86
00:04:27.740 --> 00:04:29.541
- Ms. Wilson?
- Yes.

87
00:04:29.642 --> 00:04:31.477
Emory Joy.
D.A. Durham County.

88
00:04:31.577 --> 00:04:33.980
Can't tell you how much I
appreciate you taking the time.

89
00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:35.314
Oh. not a problem.

90
00:04:35.414 --> 00:04:36.916
And you're not
the first jurisdiction

91
00:04:37.016 --> 00:04:38.217
to make the request.

92
00:04:38.317 --> 00:04:39.786
Uh. you get my email
with the case file?

93
00:04:39.886 --> 00:04:42.554
Yes. um. Kaliyah Burke
and her daughter Avery

94
00:04:42.655 --> 00:04:44.757
- reported missing.
- Four years ago. Presumed dead.

95
00:04:44.857 --> 00:04:47.526
Back when most of this area
was under water.

96
00:04:47.593 --> 00:04:50.763
and nobody would've ever
anticipated a drought.

97
00:04:50.863 --> 00:04:52.331
That's her car?

98
00:04:52.431 --> 00:04:54.300
It is. And her four-year-old

99
00:04:54.433 --> 00:04:57.269
daughter Avery
was stuffed in the trunk.

100
00:05:01.340 --> 00:05:02.709
You all right?

101
00:05:03.943 --> 00:05:05.945
Did you find
Kaliyah Burke's body?

102
00:05:06.078 --> 00:05:07.446
No.

103
00:05:07.546 --> 00:05:11.250
This is all so...
heartbreaking. um. but...

104
00:05:11.317 --> 00:05:13.152
I'm sorry. D.A. Joy.
what makes you think

105
00:05:13.285 --> 00:05:14.954
this has anything to do
with the Sicarius killer?

106
00:05:15.054 --> 00:05:17.489
We conducted a search
of the immediate area

107
00:05:17.623 --> 00:05:19.125
and uncovered this.

108
00:05:20.727 --> 00:05:23.896
- A Haeberlin case.
- An empty kill kit?

109
00:05:23.996 --> 00:05:27.066
Same as the ones used by
the Sicarius killer. am I right?

110
00:05:27.166 --> 00:05:30.737
<i>Yes. but you know
as well as I do</i>

111
00:05:30.803 --> 00:05:34.306
<i>Elias Voit confessed
to the murders of 63 people.</i>

112
00:05:35.274 --> 00:05:38.010
<i>Kaliyah Burke and her daughter
were not among them.</i>

113
00:05:38.144 --> 00:05:39.746
<i>So why keep that to himself?</i>

114
00:05:39.812 --> 00:05:41.613
<i>I don't know.</i>

115
00:05:41.714 --> 00:05:43.916
<i>That's what we need to ask him.</i>

116
00:05:54.260 --> 00:05:55.394
<i>Luke.</i>

117
00:05:55.494 --> 00:05:57.764
- you are a lifesaver.
- I'm just glad

118
00:05:57.864 --> 00:05:59.766
I didn't have
to rescue you from that

119
00:05:59.832 --> 00:06:02.501
river of water that was coming
from your busted pipe.

120
00:06:02.601 --> 00:06:04.103
Three. Three inspections.

121
00:06:04.170 --> 00:06:05.938
and nobody notices
that it's about to burst?

122
00:06:06.005 --> 00:06:09.876
Everything hangs on
just until escrow closes.

123
00:06:10.009 --> 00:06:13.212
Yup. And. uh. between the move

124
00:06:13.345 --> 00:06:15.647
and Henry applying to colleges.

125
00:06:15.748 --> 00:06:17.149
I don't know
how many more disruptions

126
00:06:17.249 --> 00:06:18.517
he and Michael can take.

127
00:06:18.650 --> 00:06:22.254
I don't think
I've seen them smile in weeks.

128
00:06:23.089 --> 00:06:24.824
How long are you out for?

129
00:06:24.891 --> 00:06:26.893
Uh. contractor said two.

130
00:06:26.993 --> 00:06:28.560
maybe three weeks.

131
00:06:28.694 --> 00:06:30.129
Ha.

132
00:06:30.196 --> 00:06:32.398
Oh. I don't think...

133
00:06:32.531 --> 00:06:36.035
the boys and I can impose
on Penelope that long.

134
00:06:36.135 --> 00:06:37.536
Oh. my gosh. Hello.

135
00:06:37.636 --> 00:06:39.238
Hello. hello.

136
00:06:39.371 --> 00:06:41.307
Ah. you are here. JJ.
and you are here. Luke.

137
00:06:41.373 --> 00:06:42.875
earlier than
I thought you'd be here.

138
00:06:42.975 --> 00:06:44.276
Oh. that's my bad.

139
00:06:44.376 --> 00:06:45.912
I just... I-I just thought

140
00:06:46.045 --> 00:06:49.215
that I should get settled
sooner rather than later.

141
00:06:49.315 --> 00:06:51.150
That makes so much sense.

142
00:06:51.250 --> 00:06:53.185
This is most awkward.
The thing is...

143
00:06:53.252 --> 00:06:55.221
No. You know what?
Uh. I'm the one that said 10:00.

144
00:06:55.321 --> 00:06:58.624
- and I just. blah.
- Penelope. do you have a guest?

145
00:07:02.661 --> 00:07:04.563
- I had a great time.
- Yeah. me too.

146
00:07:04.696 --> 00:07:07.199
I'll. um...
I'll call you later?

147
00:07:07.299 --> 00:07:09.335
Uh-huh. Yeah. Great. Bye.

148
00:07:09.401 --> 00:07:11.503
- Nice.
- Now.

149
00:07:14.106 --> 00:07:16.308
Huh.

150
00:07:17.543 --> 00:07:19.912
Okay. look. I know I'm the one
that barged in on you.

151
00:07:20.012 --> 00:07:22.214
but. uh.
I'm a little disappointed

152
00:07:22.281 --> 00:07:23.682
you didn't tell me
you had a new boyfriend.

153
00:07:23.749 --> 00:07:25.251
Oh. he's not my boyfriend.

154
00:07:25.384 --> 00:07:28.120
No. No. that's. uh.
Mr. Wednesday?

155
00:07:28.254 --> 00:07:29.421
- Yeah.
- Mr. Wednesday.

156
00:07:29.521 --> 00:07:31.657
as in there's other days
of the week?

157
00:07:31.757 --> 00:07:33.092
Oh. no.

158
00:07:33.192 --> 00:07:34.760
Saturday. and that's it.

159
00:07:34.861 --> 00:07:36.795
Oh.

160
00:07:36.896 --> 00:07:38.764
Wait. and you...
you knew about this?

161
00:07:38.898 --> 00:07:41.767
No. I didn't know he was gonna
merge into Thursday. I...

162
00:07:41.868 --> 00:07:43.735
How was any of us
to know that. really?

163
00:07:43.802 --> 00:07:45.938
No. JJ. I wasn't trying
to keep a secret from you.

164
00:07:46.038 --> 00:07:47.606
And I know it's been
over a year. but it just didn't

165
00:07:47.706 --> 00:07:50.276
seem appropriate for me
to be. you know.

166
00:07:50.376 --> 00:07:52.979
spewing about my salacious

167
00:07:53.079 --> 00:07:55.581
paramour encounters to a...

168
00:07:55.681 --> 00:07:57.850
Ah. A widow.

169
00:07:57.950 --> 00:08:00.052
No. I-I get that.

170
00:08:00.119 --> 00:08:02.754
But. hey. starting right now.

171
00:08:02.855 --> 00:08:05.291
I am gonna
be giving you the deep cuts

172
00:08:05.391 --> 00:08:06.725
about my romantic encounters.

173
00:08:06.792 --> 00:08:09.728
'Cause we are roommates.
So. strap in. get ready.

174
00:08:09.828 --> 00:08:11.964
I'm a little scared. but. uh...

175
00:08:12.064 --> 00:08:15.467
uh. honestly. though.
thank you for letting us stay.

176
00:08:15.567 --> 00:08:18.237
It is my honor
and my pleasure to host you all.

177
00:08:18.304 --> 00:08:20.006
I have... The boys' guest room

178
00:08:20.139 --> 00:08:22.574
is ready. and my gigantic bed.

179
00:08:22.641 --> 00:08:25.744
which is perfect
for platonic overnights. too.

180
00:08:25.844 --> 00:08:27.813
- I'm gonna change the sheets.
- Well. are you sure?

181
00:08:27.947 --> 00:08:30.116
'Cause I did bring my
sleeping bag out of retirement.

182
00:08:30.182 --> 00:08:32.584
Oh. no. You can save that
for the weekend camping trip

183
00:08:32.651 --> 00:08:34.053
you're gonna have
with your kids.

184
00:08:34.153 --> 00:08:37.656
Oh. uh. well. you know.
given the circumstances.

185
00:08:37.756 --> 00:08:40.092
that has been put on hold
indefinitely.

186
00:08:40.192 --> 00:08:41.760
- Oh.
- I'm gonna...

187
00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:43.562
Yeah.

188
00:08:47.399 --> 00:08:50.169
- Hey.
- What are you thinking?

189
00:08:50.269 --> 00:08:52.871
That the Jareau family needs
a pick-me-up.

190
00:08:52.972 --> 00:08:55.341
And I have an idea
if you're with me.

191
00:08:55.474 --> 00:08:57.009
Yeah.

192
00:08:57.109 --> 00:08:58.945
Attaboy.

193
00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:03.082
<i>After your Uncle Cyrus</i>

194
00:09:03.182 --> 00:09:05.051
<i>was granted legal custody.</i>

195
00:09:05.151 --> 00:09:06.818
<i>after your parents
passed away...</i>

196
00:09:06.885 --> 00:09:08.354
<i>You mean after I killed them?</i>

197
00:09:09.188 --> 00:09:11.757
After you killed them.

198
00:09:11.857 --> 00:09:13.225
How long was it before Cyrus

199
00:09:13.325 --> 00:09:15.294
starting taking you
along with him?

200
00:09:17.396 --> 00:09:20.232
Help me!

201
00:09:26.238 --> 00:09:28.140
Not long. Maybe a month.

202
00:09:29.375 --> 00:09:30.676
Didn't take him long
to break me.

203
00:09:30.742 --> 00:09:32.844
and then I was his son.

204
00:09:32.911 --> 00:09:34.513
<i>His servant.</i>

205
00:09:34.580 --> 00:09:36.315
<i>Did he use you
to lure his victims?</i>

206
00:09:36.415 --> 00:09:37.716
No. at first. he just wanted me

207
00:09:37.816 --> 00:09:39.818
to help him
get rid of the bodies.

208
00:09:39.918 --> 00:09:41.153
You know where we are?

209
00:09:41.253 --> 00:09:42.421
No.

210
00:09:42.521 --> 00:09:45.157
What'd you see
on our way out here?

211
00:09:45.224 --> 00:09:47.793
Nothing.

212
00:09:47.893 --> 00:09:49.261
Exactly.

213
00:09:49.395 --> 00:09:52.231
No road signs. no mile markers.

214
00:09:53.966 --> 00:09:55.834
That's why I picked this place.

215
00:09:58.237 --> 00:10:00.406
- Were they all in Durham County?
- Yeah.

216
00:10:00.506 --> 00:10:03.142
He thought the sheriffs there
were lazy and stupid.

217
00:10:03.242 --> 00:10:05.511
Do you remember
how many victims?

218
00:10:05.611 --> 00:10:07.346
Fifteen.

219
00:10:07.413 --> 00:10:09.548
Maybe 20.

220
00:10:09.648 --> 00:10:12.518
<i>- All buried?
- Mostly. I mean. we put</i>

221
00:10:12.584 --> 00:10:14.520
some in the river.

222
00:10:14.620 --> 00:10:16.922
a couple in the lake.

223
00:10:17.756 --> 00:10:20.659
Would you be able
to help us locate the remains?

224
00:10:22.894 --> 00:10:24.396
Well. between the lye
and the elements.

225
00:10:24.463 --> 00:10:27.533
Cyrus made pretty sure
that they'd never be found.

226
00:10:29.235 --> 00:10:31.437
If you don't mind me asking...

227
00:10:31.570 --> 00:10:33.105
since a lot of this stuff
is already part

228
00:10:33.205 --> 00:10:35.374
of the court record...
why conduct these interviews?

229
00:10:35.474 --> 00:10:38.277
- You sound a little frustrated.
- It's not a waste of time?

230
00:10:38.410 --> 00:10:40.212
I mean...

231
00:10:40.312 --> 00:10:43.282
it's pretty much
our whole raison d'être.

232
00:10:43.415 --> 00:10:46.785
Right? Analyzing behavior.

233
00:10:46.918 --> 00:10:48.287
- Right.
- Yeah.

234
00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:50.789
- And we have his profile.
- We do.

235
00:10:50.889 --> 00:10:52.424
We have his profile.
but we do not know

236
00:10:52.524 --> 00:10:53.792
how that profile evolved.

237
00:10:53.892 --> 00:10:55.827
That's why we sat down
with DeSalvo

238
00:10:55.961 --> 00:10:57.296
and Kemper and Bundy.

239
00:10:57.429 --> 00:10:58.964
And that's why
we're sitting down with Voit.

240
00:10:59.065 --> 00:11:02.134
so that we can learn how
Lee Duval became Elias Voit

241
00:11:02.234 --> 00:11:04.002
became Sicarius.

242
00:11:04.103 --> 00:11:05.604
All right.

243
00:11:05.704 --> 00:11:08.107
So. do you think it's possible
that one day we might be able

244
00:11:08.207 --> 00:11:11.077
to discern some hidden pattern
shared by all serial killers?

245
00:11:11.177 --> 00:11:12.778
Aye. there's the rub.

246
00:11:12.844 --> 00:11:15.614
While it's my hope
to discover one day

247
00:11:15.714 --> 00:11:18.984
the. uh.
unified field theory of psychos.

248
00:11:19.118 --> 00:11:21.087
it might be a false hope.

249
00:11:21.187 --> 00:11:24.823
There are always the ones
that stand out.

250
00:11:24.923 --> 00:11:28.427
Like Voit.
Maybe they are unique.

251
00:11:28.494 --> 00:11:32.331
Their own sick snowflakes.

252
00:11:43.409 --> 00:11:45.511
Shouldn't we borrow one from yours?

253
00:11:45.611 --> 00:11:47.012
